            "questionText": "An electrician is wiring a new room and connects three appliances in parallel to a single $!$120\\,\\text{V}$!$ power supply. The appliances have resistances of $!$R_1 = 60\\,\\Omega$!$, $!$R_2 = 120\\,\\Omega$!$, and $!$R_3 = 40\\,\\Omega$!$, respectively. Considering that the electrician wants to ensure the circuit breaker doesn't trip, calculate the total current (in amperes) drawn from the power supply by these appliances.",
